<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-320-016  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 320 016.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The New York Times  April 10 1990 v139 pB8(N) pC9(L) 18 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Budgeting what you already have. (Headroom, from Helix Software;SoftwareCarousel, from SoftLogic Solutions; memory-managementprograms) (Software Review) (Peripherals)(Column) (evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shannon, L.R.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Headroom 2.02 ($129), from Helix Software, and SoftwareCarousel3.0 ($89.95), from SoftLogic Solutions, are memory-managementprograms that can rejuvenate IBM PCs, XTs and ATs, providing addedmemory at much less than the price of a new system.andP;  Headroom 2.02lets a user switch between applications and memory-residentprograms easily and quickly, moving a program that is temporarilysuspended to either extended or expanded memory, or to a harddisk.andP;  With enough memory chips and sufficient hard-disk space, auser can control as much as 32Mbytes of applications andmemory-resident utilities.andP;  Headroom mediates betweenmemory-resident programs that might otherwise fight for space, andHeadroom gives application programs the full amount of memory theyneed.andP;  SoftwareCarousel 3.0 is similar, allowing a user to switchamong as many as a dozen programs, but it does not includememory-resident programs.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Helix Software Company Inc. (products)SoftLogic Solutions Inc. (products).andO;Product:   IBM PC AT (Microcomputer) (evaluation)IBM PC XT (Microcomputer) (evaluation)Headroom 2.02 (Utility program) (evaluation)SoftwareCarousel 3.0 (Utility program) (evaluation).andO;Topic:     Memory ManagementMicrocomputersEvaluationMemory-Resident Software.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>